data.title: Michael Bell (Voice Actor) - Age, Family, Bio
data.meta_description: Michael Bell (Voice Actor): his birthday, what he did before fame, his family life, fun trivia facts, popularity rankings, and more.
data.text:
About

Known for his voice acting roles in such animated series as G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero, Rugrats, and The Transformers, this New York-born performer also acted in episodes of Star Trek and Dallas.

Before Fame

Early in his career, he voiced the character of Stutz on a weekend cartoon series titled The Houndcats.

Trivia

He voiced the sidekick character in a 1982 television version of The Incredible Hulk.

Family Life

He was born and raised in Brooklyn, New York. His wife, Victoria Carroll, had a career as an actress, as did his child, Ashley Bell.
